                                                 sociedade mineira do lulo sml lucapa  and operator   mining and production ·     diamond production up  to  carats ·     recovery of specials large diamonds  carats up  to  ·     weight of specials up  to  carats ·     volumes processed up  to  bcm ·     mining resumes at highervalue mining blocks  and  post angolan wet season   continued cash generation ·     usm gross diamond revenues up  taking sales for the first half of  to usm at us per carat ·     usm sml  june cash balance plus  carats held in diamond inventory   projecto lulo  exploration ·     helicopterborne time domain electromagnetic tdem survey completed over entire cacuilo valley area  results imminent ·     preliminary analysis of tdem data identified l kimberlite  km from mining block  ·     drilling program advanced  core from seven kimberlites dispatched for mineral chemistry analysis in cape town ·     preliminary exploration along the lulo river within the mining licence area successfully identifies alluvial gravels   mothae kimberlite project lesotho lucapa  ·     optimisations and plant throughput capacity modelling to enhance project economics ·     phase  mining development plan commenced including commencement of earthworks contract tenders infrastructure planning and optimisation ·     technical management team strengthened with key appointments   lucapa australia  corporate ·     usm am  june cash balance  excluding usm lulo distribution set aside in angola to fund kimberlite exploration ·     usm loan repayment repatriated from angola further usm being finalised ·     up to usm am package arranged to fund mothae acquisition and to advance phase  development ·     dual listing on londons aim market being pursued following strong interest in lucapa from the uk           introduction lucapa diamond company limited asx lom lucapa or the company is a growing diamond company with a portfolio of highquality production development and exploration assets in angola lesotho botswana and australia   lucapas flagship asset is the lulo diamond project lulo  a km concession in angolas lunda norte diamond heartland lucapa operates lulo in partnership with empresa nacional da diamantes ep endiama and rosas  petalas   lulo through mining company sociedade mineira do lulo sml generates strong cash flows mining large and premiumvalue alluvial diamonds lulo has produced angolas two biggest diamonds on record weighing  carats and  carats   lucapa and its partners are also advancing their search for the primary kimberlite sources of the exceptional alluvial diamonds with three rigs available for drilling priority kimberlite targets at lulo   to complement the highvalue production from lulo lucapa successfully bid for and acquired a  interest in the advanced highquality mothae kimberlite project in lesotho   mothae is similar to lulo in that it is known to contain large and premiumvalue diamonds it is situated in the heart of the highest  per carat cluster of kimberlite diamond producing mines in the world within km of letšeng the worlds highest  per carat kimberlite diamond mine   lucapa has also identified drilling targets at its two earlierstage exploration projects  orapa area f in botswanas prolific orapa diamond field and brooking in the west kimberley lamproite province in western australia lucapa has a primary listing on the asx and was included in the all ordinaries index on  march  lucapa has engaged panmure gordon  co as its uk advisers and is advancing plans to dual list on londons aim market   alluvial diamond mining lulo alluvial diamond mining company sml lucapa  owner and operator produced  carats of diamonds during the quarter an increase of  on the previous corresponding period table    lulo continued to regularly produce large and premiumvalue diamonds during the quarter with the number of special diamonds recovered up  to  the total weight of specials produced during the quarter was up  to  carats these specials included two  carat diamonds   the diamond production increases were generated from a  rise in mining volumes to  bulk cubic metres bcm leaving sml on track to achieve record and targeted annual production of  bcm for calendar    the grade of the diamonds recovered during the quarter improved  to  carats per  cubic metres while the average size of the diamonds recovered was steady at  carats   mining operations in april and may  were focused primarily on mining block  with access to the highervalue mining blocks  and  available in june  as ground conditions improved following the end of the angolan wet season   q  q  h  q  h  var q  to q  var h  to h  treated m bulked             carats recovered             grade recovered cphm             no of stones recovered             avg stone size recovered             number of specials recovered             specials carat weight             diamond inventory carats               table  sml physicals and recoveries for the june quarter and prior year comparatives     alluvial diamond sales   during the quarter sml generated gross revenues of usm from three sales of lulo alluvial diamonds an increase of  on the previous corresponding quarter this took total gross sales revenues for the first half of  to usm table    the diamonds sourced primarily from mining block  achieved average sale prices of us per carat for the quarter and us per carat for the half year to june  sml finished the quarter with a cash balance of usm see corporate section in addition sml held a diamond inventory of  carats at  june table  which will be included in the next diamond sale scheduled for july    q  q  h  q  h  var q  to q  var h  to h  actual sales carats         actual sales us        actual price per carat us        actual sales a        actual price per carat a        table  lulo diamond sales and average prices for the quarter and comparative periods   alluvial exploration   mining and exploration activities at lulo have been focused on the cacuilo river valley area which runs for more than km through the south west of the lulo concession   during the quarter the lulo partners conducted their first exploration along the lulo river which is within the awarded km mining licence area this is with the aim of establishing economic resource areas along the much larger and longer lulo river to add to the current inferred alluvial jorc resource   this involved constructing a km road northeast from the cacuilo river mining operations to the lulo river to enable the mobile sedidrill rig to access this area   the sedidrill was successful in recovering alluvial gravels further drilling is being planned to define sufficient gravels for a bulk sample to test for diamond content quality and grade   kimberlite exploration   the lulo kimberlite exploration program is designed to locate the primary hardrock sources of the exceptional quality and value alluvial diamonds being mined along the cacuilo river valley area within the km lulo concession   exploration has historically been focused on magnetic targets identified from previous airborne aeromagnetic surveys in the alluvial areas where large and premiumvalue diamonds have been recovered and where there is also supporting geological evidence of proximal kimberlite pipes   in april  the new hanjin db drilling rig was commissioned at lulo after being shipped to angola from korea this increased to three the number of rigs available for drilling during the quarter to further the kimberlite exploration program   during the quarter an  line km helicopterborne time domain electromagnetic tdem survey was completed over the cacuilo river valley area the analysis and interpretation of this data is in the final stage with the results imminent     the tdem survey was designed to guide and update the lulo kimberlite drilling program by identifying other possible nonmagnetic kimberlites through identifying new anomalies with em conductive signatures as well as to provide further definition of known targets identified from the earlier aeromagnetic surveys   in addition the tdem survey data would also be used to locate alluvium channels that could assist in mapping new alluvial diamond deposits along the cacuilo river   as announced to the asx on  may  preliminary analysis of the tdem data resulted in the discovery of the coarse nearsurface l kimberlite located km upstream of mining block    core from l was included in the first batch of kimberlite drill core samples dispatched during the quarter for laboratory analysis in cape town south africa this batch also included coarse kimberlite core samples from l l l l l and l   the laboratory analysis process involves crushing the drill core and extracting kimberlite indicator minerals including garnet ilmenite chrome spinel chrome diopside and zircon from heavy liquid concentrates these indicator minerals are then analysed using an electron microprobe to determine their mineral chemistry   the mineral chemistry results are used to prioritise kimberlites for follow up work including further drilling and bulk sampling the first results from the kimberlite samples currently undergoing laboratory analysis in cape town are expected in the september  quarter         mothae kimberlite project lesotho   during the previous quarter lucapa acquired a  interest in the advanced highvalue mothae kimberlite project this followed an international tender process run by the government of the kingdom of lesotho who has retained a  interest   mothae is considered complementary to lulo in that both resources are known to host large and premiumvalue diamonds a sector of the diamond industry that has seen pricing remain robust mothae is located at the heart of the highestprice cluster of kimberlite mines in the world and within km of londonlisted gem diamonds letseng mine the worlds highest  per carat kimberlite diamond mine   lucapa notes the recent announcement by gem diamonds on july  of the recovery of a  carat dcolour type iia gem from letseng which closely followed two  carat diamond recoveries in june    the highvalue nature of the mothae resource is also reflected in the independent jorc resource estimate of more than  million carats of diamonds at a modelled average diamond value of us per carat at a mm bottom cutoff size  this is the second highest average price per carat of any kimberlite resource in the world while the jorc classified resource has been estimated to a depth of m independent modelling of the mothae kimberlite pipe extends to m see asx announcement  march    under the phase  development plan lucapa plans to process  million tonnes of mainly weathered nearsurface kimberlite material at  tonnes per annum over the first three years this material is primarily freedig which means it will require limited drilling and blasting  lucapa will commence detailed studies for the phase  development plan for mothae once phase  is fully commissioned   lucapa is able to fasttrack mine development at mothae because the  hectare kimberlite pipe has already been well defined through drilling and trial mining the trial mining produced more than  carats of diamonds which included individual stones of up to  carats and type iia gems these diamonds were sold for usm with individual stones achieving prices of up to us per carat   in developing mothae within the next  months lucapa will also leverage off the significant operating experience its board and management team have in lesotho including at the neighbouring letseng and kao mines      the company confirms that it is not aware of any new information or data that materially affects the information included in the original market announcement and that all material assumptions and technical parameters underpinning the mothae resource estimate in the relevant market announcement continue to apply and have not materially changed  the company confirms that the form and context in which the competent persons findings are presented have not been materially modified from the original market announcement during the quarter lucapa undertook multiple work streams to advance its phase  development plan for mothae these included ·     optimising mine planning and plant throughput modelling ·     updating the financial and production modelling to determine optimisation impact on project economics ·     environmental audit and approval applications ·     commenced the tendering process for large contracts and contractors ·     development infrastructure planning including plant slimes and fresh water dam locations ·     commencement of earth works and upgrading of accommodation units ·     strengthening the technical management team   orapa area f botswana   lucapas orapa area f project is located km east of the prolific orapa diamond mine in botswana previous exploration work carried out by lucapa was successful in defining a doublelobed coincident gravitymagnetic feature at the an anomaly measuring approximately m x m   during the quarter lucapa commenced the environmental approval process to drill an a drilling contract is being finalised with drilling of the an anomaly expected to commence during the current september  quarter   brooking diamond project western australia   lucapas brooking diamond project is located within km of the ellendale diamond field in western australias kimberley district which was formerly the worlds leading producer of rare fancy yellow diamonds   previous exploration work carried out by lucapa identified a series of welldefined conductors at brooking potentially associated with lamproite a host rock for diamonds   during the quarter lucapa commenced planning for a heritage survey over the areas at brooking where drilling is planned this survey is expected to be completed soon enabling drilling to commence later in the september  quarter   corporate   lucapa cash balance   at  june  lucapa held cash reserves of usm am in addition lulo mining company sml lucapa  owner and operator held cash of us million at  june    lucapas cash balance included usm in lulo loan repayments repatriated from angola during the quarter  the repatriation process for the final usm portion of the loan repayment due to lucapa is expected to be completed this quarter   lucapas usm cash balance does not include the usm distribution paid to the company in the previous quarter see asx announcement  march  as previously advised lucapa will repatriate its capital loan repayments from lulo mining company sml but will set aside and leave in angola its  share of the alluvial distributions declared to the sml partners to fund the ongoing lulo kimberlite exploration program   during the quarter lucapa received usm in proceeds from the conversion of  unlisted a options by directors and management the remaining unlisted a options expired on  april  and       may    mothae funding package   on  may  lucapa announced a funding package of up to usm am to fund the acquisition of mothae and to advance the phase  development plan   this funding see asx announcement  may  comprised   ·     am underwriting agreement with westar capital ltd for the m listed a options asx lomoa due to expire on  september    ·     am sixmonth bridging loan facility with first class securities ltd and   ·     the issue to westar of m unlisted a fee options expiring twelve months from the date of issue expected to be around  september  if exercised these fee options will generate additional cash proceeds of up to am for lucapa   under the staged payment timetable for the usm consideration for mothae lucapa originally scheduled to make the second usm payment to the government of lesotho during the quarter however in agreement with the government this payment was deferred until after the countrys national general elections which were held in early june    with the elections now concluded the new government and new ministers sworn in the government of lesotho and lucapa are meeting in lesotho shortly to conclude the payment formalities lucapa will pay the government of lesotho the usm second payment in july  and commence the monthly payments of us over the following eight months to complete the us million consideration   aim listing   in  lucapa appointed london firm panmure gordon  co as its uk advisers as part of plans to consider a dual listing on londons aim market   lucapa continues to visit london to present to uk institutional investors and funds to promote lucapa and outline the companys development plans for lulo and the highvalue mothae kimberlite   the positive feedback from these road shows has prompted lucapa to commit to plans for a dual listing on londons aim market as a result preparations for the aim listing are being advanced with lucapa shares expected to be trading on the aim market in the december  quarter   lucapa believes that the aim listing will help the company achieve its objective of attracting institutional and cornerstone investors to its share register   brooking consideration   during the quarter lucapa issued  fully paid ordinary shares and  unlisted a options expiring  may  to leopold diamond company ltd for an  interest in the brooking diamond project tenements as set out in the asx announcement of  october    orapa consideration   during the quarter lucapa issued  unlisted a options expiring  may  subject to vesting conditions as consideration for the  interest in the orapa area f project not already owned by lucapa   for and on behalf of the lucapa board                                    stephen wetherall managing director schedule of tenements as at  june  country type size km period interest  end date angola exploration primary kimberlite   years   angola exploration secondary alluvial   years   angola mining secondary alluvial   years   lesotho mining license   years   botswana reconnaissance   years   australia exploration license   years   australia exploration license   years   australia exploration license   years    these year license extensions were approved by the angolan minister of geology  mines in november  and require the attaching mining investment contract to be finalised this is currently underway   ecompetent persons statement information included in this announcement that relates to exploration results and resource estimates is based on and fairly represents information and supporting documentation prepared and compiled by albert thamm msc fausimm cp who is a corporate member of the australasian institute of mining and metallurgy  mr thamm is a director of lucapa diamond company limited  mr thamm has sufficient experience which is relevant to the style of mineralisation and type of deposit under consideration and to the activity which he is undertaking to qualify as a competent person as defined in the  edition of the australasian code for reporting exploration results mineral resources and ore reserves mr thamm and consents to the inclusion in the announcement of the matters based on this information in the form and context in which it appears no new information to the extent that announcement contains references to prior exploration results and mineral resource estimates which have been cross referenced to previous market announcements made by the company unless explicitly stated no new information is contained the company confirms that it is not aware of any new information or data that materially affects the information included in the relevant market announcements and in the case of estimates of mineral resources that all material assumptions and technical parameters underpinning the estimates in the relevant market announcement continue to apply and have not materially changed forwardlooking statements this announcement has been prepared by the company this document contains background information about the company and its related entities current at the date of this announcement this is in summary form and does not purport to be all inclusive or c